HEADWORD: Parablast
<hw>Par"a*blast</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Gr. <?/ to
grow beside. See <er>Para-</er>, and <er>-blast</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A portion of the mesoblast (of peripheral
origin) of the developing embryo, the cells of which are especially
concerned in forming the first blood and blood vessels.</def> <rj><au>C.
S. Minot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

